# FORJD Cursor Rules

Enforceable coding constraints. Product briefing lives in `AGENTS.md`.
Follow these unless the user explicitly overrides them.

## Naming
- Platform: FORJD
- Backend: forjd-backend / `backend/`
- Frontend: forjd-frontend / `frontend/`
- UI library: forjd-ui / `frontend/libs/forjd-ui/`
- Engine: forjd-engine / `engine/` (Rust core; `cdylib` + `rlib` for future Python interop)

## Engine (Rust)
- Manage with Cargo (`cargo test` / `cargo build`). Keep the crate root at `engine/src/lib.rs`.
- One binary `forjd-engine`: Arrow/Parquet process (`server`) + data plane (`data-plane` → outbox/ingest/probes via `FORJD_ROLE`).
- Stack: tokio + serde + tracing; Arrow/Parquet; axum; sqlx/redis behind `data-plane`.
- Prefer stability when bumping Arrow majors — pin below latest if needed; Arrow 52 is broken with current chrono.
- Fly deploy: single app via `engine/Dockerfile` + `engine/fly.toml` (`--features server,data-plane`).

## Backend
- Python requires 3.12+; this repo pins **3.12** (Pathway’s beartype pin breaks on 3.14) — prefer stability when choosing majors.
- Manage deps with **uv** only (`uv add` / `uv sync` / `uv lock`). Do not use pip as the primary workflow.
- Stack: FastAPI + Prefect 3 + Pathway + Polars + Dragonfly + Postgres.
- Async-first, strong typing, Pydantic v2 / pydantic-settings.
- Layout: `app/core`, `app/api/v1`, `app/pipelines`, `app/models`, `app/services` (optional `app/services/ml` for torch).

## Data tooling
- **Pathway** = continuous / incremental stream processing.
- **Polars** = finite batch DataFrames (ETL, reports, offline transforms).
- Never use Polars as a substitute for Pathway streaming jobs.
- Separation: FastAPI = API, Prefect = orchestration, Pathway = streams, Polars = batch tables.

## Frontend
- Latest stable Angular (project is on v22; floor is v18+).
- Standalone components + Signals by default.
- Build UI in `libs/forjd-ui/` (generate with `ng generate library`); consume from `frontend`.
- No heavy component libraries for core primitives (avoid Angular Material there).
- Product frontend is a static FJORD landing; optional forjd-ui library uses FJORD tokens via `--fj-*` CSS variables (no full operational console).
- Accessibility: aim for WCAG AA on new UI.
- Storybook: add `*.stories.ts` next to each forjd-ui component; publish visuals with Chromatic.
- Precision and density over flashy design.

## Docker
- Multi-stage builds mandatory.
- Prefer distroless or slim final images.
- Non-root: `USER 1001`.
- Pin specific stable image tags (no floating `:latest` in production Compose).

## Security & ops
- Strict input validation on the API.
- CORS from settings; secrets never committed.
- Structured logging to stdout.
- Liveness: `/health`. Readiness: `/ready` (dependency checks).
- Rate limiting: implemented via `app/core/rate_limit.py` (config-gated: `RATE_LIMIT_ENABLED`, per-bucket RPM settings). Do not invent a second limiter.
- Upgrade deps cautiously (`uv lock --upgrade`); one major component at a time; test after updates.

## Secrets map
- Backend: `backend/.env` (from `backend/.env.example`) — `ROLLBAR_ACCESS_TOKEN`, `POSTGRES_DSN` (Supabase), `REDIS_URL` (Dragonfly local or Fly `.internal`), `PREFECT_API_URL`, optional `API_KEY`, CORS, etc.
- Dragonfly on Fly: `DFLY_requirepass` via `fly secrets` (`infra/dragonfly/`).
- Engine on Fly: deploy from `engine/` (`fly.toml` + `Dockerfile`); `ENGINE_URL=http://forjd-engine.internal:8080` + `ENGINE_API_TOKEN`; data plane via `FORJD_ROLE=all`, `DATABASE_URL`/`POSTGRES_DSN`, `REDIS_URL`, optional `FORJD_INTERNODE_*`; apply schema through `sql/026` (production path `003`–`026`; see `backend/sql/README.md`).
- Chromatic / frontend CI: `CHROMATIC_PROJECT_TOKEN` (root `.env` or CI secrets).
- Never commit real tokens. Empty optional tokens disable those integrations.

## Comments
- Use minimal **section comments** so a reader can scan what each block does.
- Style: `# --- Title ---` (Python/SQL/Rust) or `// --- Title ---` (TS/JS). One line preferred.
- Do not narrate obvious syntax; do mark auth, E2EE, and security boundaries.
- Details: `.cursor/rules/section-comments.mdc`.

## Quality gates

See `AGENTS.md` → **Quality gates** for the canonical per-component commands. Summary:
- Backend: `cd backend && uv run ruff check . && uv run ruff format --check . && uv run python -m unittest discover -s tests`
- Engine: `cd engine && cargo fmt --check && cargo clippy --all-targets --features server,data-plane -- -D warnings && cargo test --features server,data-plane`
- Frontend: `cd frontend && npx ng test --no-watch` and `npm run build`
- CI: `.github/workflows/backend-ci.yml` and `.github/workflows/frontend-ci.yml`

## Security invariants

- E2EE sealed lane: FORJD stores and routes ciphertext only; the pipeline never receives plaintext event content.
- Tenant isolation: all data access enforced via Postgres RLS + `require_tenant_access`; no cross-tenant reads.
- Never accept partner end-user tokens at the FORJD edge; only tenant-bound `fjsvc_` service tokens or Supabase user JWTs.
- Rate limiting is implemented solely via `app/core/rate_limit.py` (`RATE_LIMIT_ENABLED`). Do not add a second limiter.

## LOG.MD
- `LOG.MD` is an **engineering journal (historical)**; it is not the architecture contract. Current architecture lives in `ARCHITECTURE.md` and `AGENTS.md`.
- Append an entry after meaningful progress (optional). Format: `- YYYY-MM-DD: Brief description of what and why (1–2 sentences).`
- Specific enough to remember the journey (commands, decisions, challenges) — not a novel, not a one-word stub.
- Example: `- 2026-07-14: Initialized backend with uv + FastAPI + Prefect + Pathway. Chose Prefect for Pythonic workflow config over Airflow.`
- Keep the **Packages** section current: when adding/removing a direct dependency, add/remove its GitHub (or primary) repo URL so packages can be starred. See `.cursor/rules/packages-log.mdc`.
